<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567006>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Odontostilbe pulchra, syntype MNHN 0000-9593, female 28.7 mm SL (top), a specimen INHS 40101, male 32.3 mm SL from Trinidad(middle top), and specimensMCP 38863, male 28.6 mm SL (middle bottom), andfemale 32.5 mm SL (bottom) from río Orinoco basin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567006/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5070321>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Pectoral-fin length as a function of standard length for males of Odontostilbe pulchra, against O. fugitiva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/5070321/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567012>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Anal-fin base length as a function of standard length for males of Odontostilbe pulchra, against O. fugitiva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567012/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567014>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Snout length as a function of head length for males of Odontostilbe pulchra, against O. splendida, and O. pao." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567014/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567010>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Upper jaw length as a function of head length for males, females and unsexed specimens of Odontostilbe pulchra, against O. fugitiva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567010/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567016>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Dentition of Odontostilbe pulchra, INHS 40101, male 32.5 mm SL:left premaxilla (top), maxilla (middle), and dentary (bottom), lateral view. Scanning electron micrograph (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567016/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567022>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. First gill arch of Odontostilbe pulchra: left side, lateral view, showing gill gland (top) of FMNH 84037, male 26.6 mm SL, in detail gill rakers on upper branchial branch (middle), and gill rakers on lower branchial branch (bottom) of MCP 38863, male 27.2mm SL.Scanningelectron micrographs (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567022/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567028>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Snout length as a function of head length for males against females of Odontostilbe pulchra." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567028/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4567030>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Distribution of Odontostilbe pulchra. Circles (material examined, symbols can represent more than one lot, and more than one locality). In detail Trinidad map, modified from American Geographical Society of New York (1957)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/4567030/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

